# API greenfield (non-negotiable)

When the user says **greenfield**, **new API**, or work under `packages/api/`:

**Plan:** `packages/api/docs/greenfield-plan.md` ¬∑ **Guard:** `composer --working-dir packages/api greenfield:guard`

## Definition

Build a **new Laravel application** that matches the **HTTP contract** (paths, status codes, JSON shapes in `packages/api/openapi/openapi.json`).  
**Do not** preserve legacy architecture, class names, or call paths.

**Contract parity ‚âÝ code parity.** Read old behavior only to write tests and reimplement logic.

## Required architecture

- **HTTP:** `routes/api.php` ‚Üí invokable controllers (or small controllers) ‚Üí Form Requests ‚Üí API Resources
- **Logic:** `app/Services/{Domain}/` ‚Äî constructor injection, instance methods
- **Persistence:** Eloquent models + migrations for app tables (`users`, `principals`, `app_settings`, ‚Ä¶), or `DB::` query builder ‚Äî **not** raw `\PDO` passed through the stack
- **Config:** Laravel `config/` + `.env`; bridge `wgw-config.php` once in a service provider ‚Äî **not** `Config::load()` in domain code
- **Auth:** Laravel guard or dedicated auth service using the DB layer ‚Äî **not** `ApiAuth::authenticateBearer($pdo)` with superglobals
- **Tests:** Pest feature tests per route group **before** calling a domain ‚Äúdone‚Äù
- **Files:** Laravel **Flysystem** via `WgwStorage` / `Storage` disks ‚Äî shared by REST (drive, notes, office) and WebDAV file tree (see `api-storage-flysystem.mdc`)

## Forbidden (migration theater)

Do **not** do these and call it greenfield:

- Rename/move folders (`wgw-src` ‚Üí `app/`) and keep the same static classes
- `*ApiService` that only forwards to `MailApi`, `DriveKernel`, `*Kernel`, `*Static`
- Monolithic `DomainRouteService` routing all domains
- `WgwRuntime` / `$_SERVER` shims so legacy code can run unchanged
- `ApiResultReady` or exception-based ‚Äúfake returns‚Äù instead of real service return types
- New `*Kernel` / `*Static` classes
- `public static function ‚Ä¶(\PDO $pdo)` domain APIs
- Stock `App\Models\User` (Laravel scaffold) while real users live in Sabre tables without a model
- ‚ÄúThin wrapper‚Äù PRs without deleting the legacy entry point they wrap
- Direct filesystem I/O in domain code (`Paths::data()`, `file_put_contents`, `readfile`) instead of Flysystem

## Sabre / DAV exception

WebDAV may keep a **thin** `dav.php` + Sabre PDO backends for Cal/Card. **File** WebDAV must use the **same Flysystem disks** as REST ‚Äî not `Paths::data().'/files'` in `SabreApp` only. Plugins call Laravel **services** backed by storage, not duplicate path logic.

## When unsure

Stop and ask: *‚ÄúShould I reimplement this operation in a new Service, or is there an approved legacy boundary?‚Äù*  
Default answer for REST: **reimplement.**
